  "title": "Technician (Electrical / Mechanical)",
  "description": "<p>* Perform routine and preventative maintenance on terminal equipment, such as bucket elevators, air slides, </p>\n<p>   compressors, and other mechanical systems.</p>\n<p>* Diagnose and troublesshoot mechanical and electrical issues to ensure minimal downntime and efficient </p>\n<p>   operations.</p>\n<p>* Ensure that all tools and equipment are in safe and optimal working condition, making necessary repairs</p>\n<p>   and adjustments as required.</p>\n<p>* Monitor and manage the flow of cement products within the terminal inclusive of ship receiving and bulk</p>\n<p>   loading to ensure efficient handling and storage.</p>\n<p>* Maintain accurate records of maintenance activities, equipment performance, and any issues that arise.</p>\n<p>* Work collaboratively with other team members to achieve operational goals.</p>\n<p>* Higher Nitec or Diploma holders in Electrical /Mechanical /Automation Engineering</p>\n<p>* 1-2 years of experience a Technician in the cement terminal industry</p>\n<p>* Forklift license or Welder certificate is a plus</p>\n<p>* Abilty to work in a cement terminal environment, which may include exposure to dust, noise, and varying</p>\n<p>   temperatures</p>\n<p>* Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail</p>\n<p>* Able to work independently and as part of the team</p>",
